{"key":"post-11439556","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11439556</id>\n<content>The reason you don't want to heat a fruiting chamber is it robs your humidity to form condensation on the walls.&amp;nbsp; Condensation forms on the warm side of a surface with a temperature differential.&amp;nbsp; It's better to heat the room so that it isn't warmer inside the terrarium than outside the terrarium.&amp;nbsp; Find a room with a bright window.&amp;nbsp; You'll probably get enough daytime solar heating to do the trick for you.&amp;nbsp; 60F at night is fine, as long as it warms up ten to fifteen degrees during the day.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11439562</next>\n<prev>11439527</prev>\n<first>11438721</first>\n<last>11958515</last>\n<when>1258045865</when>\n<utime>11/12/09 07:11 PM</utime>\n</post>"}